-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Requirements
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
screen-session  requires a recent version of Screen patched with gnu_screen.diff
screen-session uses "ps", "pgrep" and reads /proc filesystem.

tested on:
linux, python 2.5.2
freebsd 8.1, python 2.6.5 (with mounted procfs)
opensolaris, python 2.4.4

gnu_screen.diff changes:
- add "tty" command
- add "regionsize" command
- make "group" queryable
- associate focuminsize with the layout
- add "dumpscreen window|layout" command


-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Installation
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (screen-session is installed 
into the /usr/ namespace by default), you can also disable colors 
by removing "-DCOLOR".


Afterwards enter the following command to build and install 
screen-session (if necessary as root):

    make clean install


Make sure you have a recent version of Screen and apply the necessary 
patch (gnu_screen.diff):

    git clone git://git.sv.gnu.org/screen.git screen; cd screen
    
    git-apply ../screen-session-${VERSION}/gnu_screen.diff

    cd src; autoreconf; autoheader; 
    
    ./configure && make

    sudo make install

